Name: &5&lA soothing melody
Description: Music is said to be one of the most powerful forces of nature. And in times of trouble, that is exactly what you need!
SendMessage:
&2&lIncoming Pokégear Call

  &bStatera HQ&r is trying to reach you.

Dialog.&3&lStatera: Hey [PLAYER], it looks like you just entered &lSpiritvale&r from what our GPS is showing, can you check out the area for us?
There has been more suspicious Pokémon activity again and we need you to help the locals.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: I'll get right to it!
Dialog.&3&lStatera: We'll be checking in with you later, thanks again!

Objective: Investigate what's going on at all the bridges in Spiritvale
Talk to the citizens at the bridge to see how you can help calm the Pokemon

Dialog.&9&lTommy: You must be new around here...
I promise things are not normally this hectic...
I wish this wasn't your first impression of &lSpiritvale&r...

Dialog.&e&lIssa: Hey, maybe you could help us out!
Normally the Nurse handles this... She has a flute she plays to calm down the local Pokémon.
They get spooked every now and then hahaha...

Dialog.&bSparkle: Do you think you could grab the flute from her chest? She keeps it in a chest above the doorway of her house.
We'd ask her but she's away on business for &3Statera&r.

Objective: Go to Nurse Daisy's home and find her flute (Hint> Her house is near a gym structure outside of town)

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Hmm... The flute should be in the chest above the doorway!
I need to be quiet though so I don't wake up Nurse Daisy's Snorlax...

Objective: Try to find Nurse Daisy's flute in the chest

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Hmm... It looks like it needs a code!
There's a paper here...
It says 'To find the first digit of the code speak to my gardener, &6Michael&r in case of emergency'...
I guess I have to go talk to &6Michael&r!

Objective: Try to find the four digits to unlock the chest (Talk to Michael)

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Hi there! I was wondering if you have the first digit to Nurse Daisy's chest...
I need it to calm the Pokémon down...
Dialog.&6&lMichael: I might... But I need to know I can trust you! I need you to do something for me first.
Prove that you can catch and give me a normal type pokemon and the first digit of the code is yours!

Objective: Bring a Normal type Pokemon to Michael

Dialog.&6&lMichael: Thanks! Okay the first digit of the code is 9. Good luck!
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Do you know who has the second digit?
Dialog.&6&lMichael: She should be on her rounds around town delivering mail.

Objective: Find the second digit of the code by talking to Amelia

Dialog.[PLAYER]: I just need the second digit to Nurse Daisy's chest so I can get her flute!
The Pokémon are out of control again...
Dialog.&a&lAmelia: Okay then... but... I am running late on my mail rounds so I wont be able to stop by the post office today.
Could you just bring me a &egeneric postcard&r I can send to my grandma and I'll give you the second digit to the code?

ProvideItem.name: &7Generic Mail
ProvideItem.description: &fWrite a letter and sign it so that you can mail it out to another trainer

Dialog.&a&lAmelia: Perfect! Okay, get ready! The second digit is 7!
I assume you want to know where to find the third digit?
Just talk to &5Mia&r! Those 2 keep sending letters to each other. Mia must know something.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Alright! Thank you!

Objective: Find the third digit of the code by talking to Mia

Dialog.&5&lMia: Yo! What brings you here today?
Dialog.[PLAYER]: I was told you have the third digit to Nurse Daisy's chest?
Dialog.&5&lMia: I sure do! However, I have this riddle that I cannot solve. If you can help me, I will give you the code!
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Alright, what's the riddle?

Objective: Solve the riddle located near Mia (Answer by typing /youranswer)

Dialog.&5&lMia: That makes perfect sense... Great job! The third digit is 4!
Oh and &6Kevin&r has the final digit!
He is studying pokémon medicine so you can probably find him near the pokécenter.

Objective: Find the last digit of the code by talking to Kevin

Dialog.&6&lKevin: Why hello there... I've been expecting you...
Dialog.[PLAYER]: You have?
Dialog.&6&lKevin: Of course! I heard you want the final digit?
Well, I haven't battled in a while so before I give you the digit, I want to battle against a real trainer!

BattleNpc.&6&lKevin: Let's see if you are worthy for the final digit!

Dialog.&6&lKevin: I really need to get back into batteling!... The final digit is 0!

Objective: Click the chest to enter the code digit by digit (The code is 9740)

Dialog.[PLAYER]: I got it!
Uh oh! It looks like I woke up the Snorlax! It seems very angry!
Whew! That was a close call! Hey it dropped a piece of paper... Maybe that will help me!

Objective: Return to the bridge and play the flute to calm down the Pokemon

Dialog.[PLAYER]: It worked! Thank goodness!
Yeah! They sent me here to help!
Dialog.&e&lIssa: Really? They sent you out here?
Dialog.&b&lSparkle: Almost makes it seem like they care, huh?
Dialog.&d&lIggy: I've been telling you guys all along! Geez.
Stuck in the ways of old, I swear...

Dialog.&5&lTessa: I mean, it's just the fact that the Pokémon didn't start going bonkers until &3Statera&r showed up!
Dialog.&9&lTommy: Y'all shush... there's a representative coming...

Dialog.&4&lThomas: Can you come here for a moment, [PLAYER]?

Objective: Talk to Thomas at the bridge in Spiritvale.

Dialog.&4&lThomas: Thanks for doing this, I was running behind from the last time they pinged our GPS...
You did good work though, it was definitely a better decision to send you here rather than me.
Here, take this for all the trouble!
I'll take care of things from here! Good luck training for your gym battle!
